Text.Value: Ohhh, I told him I'd retired from the bounty hunting. I haven't killed a goblinoid in years.

EditorData.NodeContext: Frustrated - she and the bugbear have been over this

Text.Value: I have. Sorry, Nora - but you two aren't meant to be.
Here. It was to be a gift to him - but it would only be a reminder of what could have been. You take it.
Don't you have bigger priorities? Like the massacre that just took place?
Severn isn't scared. He used to love it when I told him of all the monsters I've slain.
Hm? Sorry, not now - need to find another way to make Severn notice me.
We're just... taking a breather. A short one.
Bah. Politics. The only battlefield that matters is that of the heart.
He's intimidated by you. Do yourself a favour and set your sights somewhere else.
Don't you have bigger priorities? Like the massacre that just took place?
Bugbears live short lives. It's destined for tragedy either way.
Oh, feign indifference all you want. You don't fool me - and you won't win him over that way.
But - what do you mean? He didn't say that!
Men. Monsters. Why are they all so bloody soft?
Here. I was saving this, to woo him - but it doesn't matter now, does it? He can't see a good thing when he has it.
It's me. Severn and I are in love.
Besides - Severn can't eat humanoid. Gives him a bellyache.
But NO funny business!
Only... I don't know why he broke things off. He said he had to - that Nine-Fingers forbade our love - but... well, I'm fairly certain she doesn't know I exist.
Eyes off the barkeep, new blood. He and I, we're a thing. Were a thing. Will be a thing again.
Don't you have bigger priorities? Like the massacre that just took place?
Please, hurry. Every moment that passes is one we could spend... together.
All great loves end - all the more important that we use the time we have!
So what I'm hearing is - you were dumped.
I will get right on that.
Perhaps for someone else, I would. But my love for Severn is pure. Unsullied by violence.
He wouldn't. But if he honestly thinks I'd believe that, well... I suppose I've driven him to desperation.
That is not what I said! We're just having... a break. A very short one.
So are all great loves. But if Severn finds it easier to wrap his heart in swaddling... well. I do not wish to cause him pain.
That is a stereotype. And an ugly one!
Go away. Love is dead, and I might as well be.
Leave.
No, no - Severn will come around. He has to.
You clearly haven't met - you wouldn't soon forget a man like him. I know I can't.
Have you spoken to Severn yet?
You're in love with the barkeep? The bugbear?
He's a bugbear. The only date you two will go on is if he decides to eat you for dinner.
Who's the barkeep?
Perhaps... he'll open up to you? He's such a soft heart, really connects with his customers. You'll see.
Why aren't you a thing right now?
You? Please. He'd break you in half. So would I.
Obviously! But he's my big bear.
You back-stabbing minx. I suppose you want to fight now, heh? Bathe in one another's blood in Severn's name?
I really, truly, could not care less.

Synopsis: Nora is a retired bounty hunter, and an over-the-top romantic who's obsessed with the bugbear bartender. We must convince her to stop her pursuit of him.
